-- Bloomsbury, Publisher of Harry Potter, Reports Business Is Performing Well
-- B y   D a r a   D o y l e
-- 2010-10-15T06:08:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/bloomsbury-publisher-of-harry-potter-says-second-half-outlook-buoyant-.html
Bloomsbury Publishing Plc, which
publishes J.K. Rowling’s Harry Potter novels, said business is
“performing well.”  “The second half is looking more buoyant than the first
with books sales improving,” the company said.“The outcome for
the year is still dependent on the level of consumer and
business to business demand between now and the end of the
financial year.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dara Doyle at 
 ddoyle1@bloomberg.net  